I'm setting the board width dynamically based on the visual viewport height and the board's aspect ratio, then constraining it to reasonable limits. The issue is that when the level completion dialog appears or before the extra moves screen shows up, the viewport height changes, which recalculates the board size smaller. Then when moving to the next level, the dimensions are off because the viewport hasn't stabilized yet.

Looking at the screenshots, Level 25 displays normally at first, but becomes compressed when the "Level Solved" screen appears. By Level 26, the board is too wide and gets cut off on the right side. The root cause seems to be that `renderBoard` is being called at different times when the viewport height has shifted—possibly due to the address bar appearing or overlays being shown—so the board dimensions end up inconsistent between levels.

Let me trace through how `nextLevel` triggers `renderBoard` to understand when these viewport changes are happening.

